# Daniel S. Weld | Semantic Scholar

[

## TriviaQA: A Large Scale Distantly Supervised Challenge Dataset for Reading Comprehension

](/paper/TriviaQA%3A-A-Large-Scale-Distantly-Supervised-for-Joshi-Choi/f010affab57b5fcf1cd6be23df79d8ec98c7289c)

[Mandar Joshi](/author/Mandar-Joshi/144863691)[Eunsol Choi](/author/Eunsol-Choi/2890423)[Daniel S. Weld](/author/Daniel-S.-Weld/1780531)[Luke Zettlemoyer](/author/Luke-Zettlemoyer/1982950)

Computer Science, Linguistics

-   1 May 2017

It is shown that, in comparison to other recently introduced large-scale datasets, TriviaQA has relatively complex, compositional questions, has considerable syntactic and lexical variability between questions and corresponding answer-evidence sentences, and requires more cross sentence reasoning to find answers.

[

## PDDL-the planning domain definition language

](/paper/PDDL-the-planning-domain-definition-language-McDermott-Ghallab/d82c6b8081343b2eae63d45feefe630233ad60e1)

[D. McDermott](/author/D.-McDermott/145313556)[M. Ghallab](/author/M.-Ghallab/2051367) [D. Wilkins](/author/D.-Wilkins/145274211)

Computer Science

-   1998

This manual describes the syntax of PDDL, the Planning Domain Definition Language, the problem-specification language for the AIPS-98 planning competition, and hopes to encourage empirical evaluation of planner performance, and development of standard sets of problems all in comparable notations.

[

## SpanBERT: Improving Pre-training by Representing and Predicting Spans

](/paper/SpanBERT%3A-Improving-Pre-training-by-Representing-Joshi-Chen/81f5810fbbab9b7203b9556f4ce3c741875407bc)

[Mandar Joshi](/author/Mandar-Joshi/144863691)[Danqi Chen](/author/Danqi-Chen/50536468)[Yinhan Liu](/author/Yinhan-Liu/11323179)[Daniel S. Weld](/author/Daniel-S.-Weld/1780531)[Luke Zettlemoyer](/author/Luke-Zettlemoyer/1982950)[Omer Levy](/author/Omer-Levy/39455775)

Computer Science

-   24 July 2019

The approach extends BERT by masking contiguous random spans, rather than random tokens, and training the span boundary representations to predict the entire content of the masked span, without relying on the individual token representations within it.

[

## Fine-Grained Entity Recognition

](/paper/Fine-Grained-Entity-Recognition-Ling-Weld/777ef98b19cac4dd83bd2318f6d29a38ea6c8294)

[Xiao Ling](/author/Xiao-Ling/145787377)[Daniel S. Weld](/author/Daniel-S.-Weld/1780531)

Computer Science

-   22 July 2012

A fine-grained set of 112 tags is defined, the tagging problem is formulates as multi-class, multi-label classification, an unsupervised method for collecting training data is described, and the FIGER implementation is presented.

[

## Knowledge-Based Weak Supervision for Information Extraction of Overlapping Relations

](/paper/Knowledge-Based-Weak-Supervision-for-Information-of-Hoffmann-Zhang/d48edf9e81653f4c3da716b037b0b50d54c5b034)

[Raphael Hoffmann](/author/Raphael-Hoffmann/2566295)[Congle Zhang](/author/Congle-Zhang/1799338)[Xiao Ling](/author/Xiao-Ling/145787377)[Luke Zettlemoyer](/author/Luke-Zettlemoyer/1982950)[Daniel S. Weld](/author/Daniel-S.-Weld/1780531)

Computer Science

-   19 June 2011

A novel approach for multi-instance learning with overlapping relations that combines a sentence-level extraction model with a simple, corpus-level component for aggregating the individual facts is presented.

[

## CORD-19: The Covid-19 Open Research Dataset

](/paper/CORD-19%3A-The-Covid-19-Open-Research-Dataset-Wang-Lo/bc411487f305e451d7485e53202ec241fcc97d3b)

[Lucy Lu Wang](/author/Lucy-Lu-Wang/31860505)[Kyle Lo](/author/Kyle-Lo/46258841) [Sebastian Kohlmeier](/author/Sebastian-Kohlmeier/41018147)

Computer Science, Medicine

NLPCOVID19

-   22 April 2020

The mechanics of dataset construction are described, highlighting challenges and key design decisions, an overview of how CORD-19 has been used, and several shared tasks built around the dataset are described.

[

## Guidelines for Human-AI Interaction

](/paper/Guidelines-for-Human-AI-Interaction-Amershi-Weld/ad3cf68bae32d21f25ac142287d4a556155619d2)

[Saleema Amershi](/author/Saleema-Amershi/1719124)[Daniel S. Weld](/author/Daniel-S.-Weld/1780531) [E. Horvitz](/author/E.-Horvitz/145479841)

Computer Science

-   2 May 2019

This work proposes 18 generally applicable design guidelines for human-AI interaction that can serve as a resource to practitioners working on the design of applications and features that harness AI technologies, and to researchers interested in the further development of human- AI interaction design principles.

[

## S2ORC: The Semantic Scholar Open Research Corpus

](/paper/S2ORC%3A-The-Semantic-Scholar-Open-Research-Corpus-Lo-Wang/5c5751d45e298cea054f32b392c12c61027d2fe7)

[Kyle Lo](/author/Kyle-Lo/46258841)[Lucy Lu Wang](/author/Lucy-Lu-Wang/31860505)[Mark Neumann](/author/Mark-Neumann/2060376981)[Rodney Michael Kinney](/author/Rodney-Michael-Kinney/143967880)[Daniel S. Weld](/author/Daniel-S.-Weld/1780531)

Computer Science

-   2020

In S2ORC, a large corpus of 81.1M English-language academic papers spanning many academic disciplines is introduced, which is expected to facilitate research and development of tools and tasks for text mining over academic text.

[

## SPECTER: Document-level Representation Learning using Citation-informed Transformers

](/paper/SPECTER%3A-Document-level-Representation-Learning-Cohan-Feldman/a3e4ceb42cbcd2c807d53aff90a8cb1f5ee3f031)

[Arman Cohan](/author/Arman-Cohan/2527954)[Sergey Feldman](/author/Sergey-Feldman/46411828)[Iz Beltagy](/author/Iz-Beltagy/46181066)[Doug Downey](/author/Doug-Downey/145612610)[Daniel S. Weld](/author/Daniel-S.-Weld/1780531)

Computer Science

-   15 April 2020

This work proposes SPECTER, a new method to generate document-level embedding of scientific papers based on pretraining a Transformer language model on a powerful signal of document- level relatedness: the citation graph, and shows that Specter outperforms a variety of competitive baselines on the benchmark.
